Problem Description

Gru has started creating army of minions.Minions are funny creatures.
So he thought of naming them.The names of the minions are supposed to formed with similar characters.So he gave them names and stored safely in alphabetical order.But a naughty minion scrambled all the names.
So gru has to again order them.Unfortunately gru has to leave for shooting of Despicable Me 3 Shooting,So he is asking for your help.

Input

The first line of the input contains an integer T denoting the number of test cases. The description of T test cases follows.
The first line in each test case contains a single integer N describing the no. of strings   
Then the next N lines   each test case contains  N strings  


Output

For each test case, output the sorted strings one in each line.

 

Constraints

1 ≤ T ≤ 100
0 ≤ N ≤ 100
1 ≤ |S| ≤ 1000

 

Example
Input:
1
4
mace
acme
ecma
came

Output:
acme
came
ecma
mace
